import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
In[16]:
import seaborn as sns
In[17]:
plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
sns.lineplot(data=df,x="Year",y="Sales_Volume",estimator="sum",ci=None,marker="*",color="orange",markersize="12")
plt.title("BMW yearly sales Trends(2012-2024)")
plt.xlabel("year")
plt.ylabel("Total sales volume")
plt.grid(True,alpha=0.3)
plt.show()
In[17]:
plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
sns.barplot(data=df,x="Region",y="Sales_Volume",estimator="sum",ci=None)
plt.title("BMW sales distribution by Region")
plt.xlabel("Region")
plt.ylabel("Total sales volume")
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.show()
In[18]:
top_models=df.groupby("Model")["Sales_Volume"].sum().sort_values(ascending=False).head(9)
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
sns.barplot(x=top_models.index,y=top_models.values)
plt.title("BMW Top best selling models")
plt.ylabel("Total sales volume")
plt.xlabel("Model")
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.show()
In[19]:
plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
sns.scatterplot(data=df,x="Engine_Size_L",y="Price_USD",hue="Fuel_Type",alpha=0.7)
plt.title("Price Vs. Engine Size(by Fuel Type)",fontsize=14)
plt.xlabel("Engine size (Liters)")
plt.ylabel("Price (USD)")
plt.legend(title="Fuel Type")
plt.show()
In[20]:

plt.xlabel("Mileage (KM)")
plt.ylabel("Price (USD)")
plt.legend(title="Region",bbox_to_anchor=(1,1))

In[22]:
numeric_df=df.select_dtypes(include=[np.number])
if len(numeric_df.columns)>=4:
    plt.figure(figsize=(5,4))
    corr=numeric_df.corr()
    sns.heatmap(corr,annot=True,cmap='coolwarm',fmt='.2f')
    plt.title('Correlation Heatmap')
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
else:
    print('Not enough numeric columns for a correlation heatmap')
